OL,3,CHeartbroken mum begs drivers not to
OL,4,Cspeed after son's death
OL,6,FIn Hampshire, officers caught one
OL,7,Fdriver travelling at 147 mph on the
OL,8,FM27, while in Kent, another driver was
OL,9,Fcaught travelling at 160 mph on the
OL,10,FM25 at Swanley.
OL,12,F"It feels like Callum's death was in
OL,13,Fvain. It's not made any difference and
OL,14,Fpeople are still speeding." said Ms
OL,15,FSlope.
OL,17,FShe added: "People don't think about
OL,18,Fconsequences, it doesn't cross their
OL,19,Fminds. It makes me feel sick when I
OL,20,Fhear a car come past that's going too
OL,21,Ffast.
